Policies & Procedures
ðŸ“š Documentation
Data Protection Policy
GDPR Compliance by Design

Data Minimization: We only collect what's necessary for review management

Purpose Limitation: Data used exclusively for stated purposes

Storage Limitation: Customer data deleted upon request or after 24 months of inactivity

Transparency: Customers can request all their data at any time

Technical Implementation:

Row-Level Security (RLS) in Supabase ensures tenant isolation

Encryption at rest: All customer data encrypted using AES-256

Encryption in transit: TLS 1.3 for all communications

Pseudonymization: Where possible, personal data is pseudonymized

Incident Response Plan
Four-Step Response Protocol:

Detection & Classification (Within 1 hour)

Automated monitoring alerts

Customer reports

Third-party notifications

Containment & Analysis (Within 4 hours)

Isolate affected systems

Log preservation

Root cause analysis

Eradication & Recovery (Within 24 hours)

Patch vulnerabilities

Restore from clean backups

Verify system integrity

Post-Incident Review (Within 7 days)

Document lessons learned

Update procedures

Notify affected parties if required by GDPR

Data Retention Policy
Customer Data:

Active customers: Retained for duration of service + 90 days

Inactive customers: Automated deletion after 24 months

Backup retention: 30 days rolling backup, encrypted

Log retention: 90 days for security logs, 30 days for application logs

Review Data:

Public reviews: Stored indefinitely (publicly available content)

Private feedback: Deleted after 90 days or upon customer request

AI training data: Never uses customer-specific data

Access Control Policy
Role-Based Access Control (RBAC):

yaml
Roles:
  Admin:
    - Full system access
    - Customer data viewing
    - Configuration changes
    - Required: MFA enabled
  
  Support:
    - Customer support view only
    - Ticket management
    - No access to billing data
  
  Customer:
    - Own company data only
    - Review management
    - Analytics viewing
Access Protocols:

MFA required for all admin accounts

Regular access reviews quarterly

Logging of all access attempts

Automated session timeout after 30 minutes

Vendor Management Policy
Third-Party Risk Assessment:

Vendor	Service	Data Shared	Compliance	Risk Level
Supabase	Database/Backend	Customer data	GDPR, SOC2	Medium
46elks	SMS Service	Phone numbers	Swedish law	Low
Claude API	AI Processing	Review text	Data processing agreement	Medium
DeepSeek API	AI Processing	Review text	Data processing agreement	Medium
Stripe	Payments	Billing data	PCI DSS, GDPR	Low
Requirements for Vendors:

Must have GDPR compliance statement

Must sign Data Processing Agreement (DPA)

Must provide SOC2/ISO certifications where applicable

Regular security assessment reviews

